  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><p><strong>1. Daily Accounting & Bookkeeping</strong></p><ul><li>Manage the <strong>full set of accounts</strong> independently.</li><li>Record and review all accounting entries, including revenue, expenses, and AR/AP.</li><li>Perform monthly <strong>bank reconciliations</strong>.</li><li>Manage petty cash and monitor daily cash flow.</li></ul><p><strong>2. Accounts Receivable (AR) & Accounts Payable (AP)</strong></p><ul><li>Issue invoices and monitor collection status/aging reports.</li><li>Process vendor payments and manage payment schedules.</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date ledgers for customers and suppliers.</li></ul><p><strong>3. Financial Reporting & Management Analysis</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements (P&L, Balance Sheet, Cash Flow).</li><li>Provide financial analysis and management reports as required by leadership.</li><li>Assist in annual <strong>budgeting</strong> and perform variance analysis (budget vs. actual).</li></ul><p><strong>4. Tax & Regulatory Compliance</strong></p><ul><li>Handle all tax filings (e.g., VAT/GST, withholding tax, and corporate income tax).</li><li>Ensure all accounting practices comply with local accounting standards and tax laws.</li><li>Coordinate with external auditors, accountants, and tax authorities.</li></ul><p><strong>5. Payroll & HR Administration</strong></p><ul><li>Calculate monthly salaries, bonuses, and overtime pay.</li><li>Manage statutory contributions (e.g., social insurance, health insurance, and pension funds).</li><li>Prepare payroll-related reports and filing documents.</li></ul><p><strong>6. Internal Control & Administrative Support</strong></p><ul><li>Establish and maintain basic internal control procedures.</li><li>Organize and archive financial documents, contracts, and sensitive records.</li><li>Provide general administrative support and handle ad-hoc tasks as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Education:</strong> Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or a related field.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Proven experience in managing <strong>full set of accounts</strong> is highly preferred.</li><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Proficiency in accounting software (e.g., QuickBooks, Xero, SAP) and <strong>Advanced Microsoft Excel</strong>.</li><li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong> * Ability to work independently with strong time-management skills.</li><li><li>High level of integrity, attention to detail, and a strong sense of confidentiality.</li><li>Problem-solving mindset and the ability to meet tight deadlines.</li></li></ul>",
